  <exercise label="Swap_01_Output">
    <title>Swap Output with 01</title>
    <idx>swap output 01</idx>
    <statement>
        <p>What is the output of the SWAP gate with |01> as the input?</p>
    </statement>
    <choices randomize="no">
      <choice>
        <statement><p>|00> or <datafile label="Balls00" filename="Balls00.png" include-source="yes">
          <image source="Balls00.png" width="66%"/>
        </datafile>
      </p></statement>
        <feedback><p>Make sure you hooked up your circuit correctly!</p>
         </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement><p>|01> or <datafile label="Balls01" filename="Balls01.png" include-source="yes">
          <image source="Balls01.png" width="66%"/>
        </datafile>
      </p></statement>
        <feedback><p>Make sure you hooked up your circuit correctly!</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="yes">
        <statement><p>|10> or <datafile label="Balls10" filename="Balls10.png" include-source="yes">
          <image source="Balls10.png" width="66%"/>
        </datafile></p></statement>
        <feedback><p>Yes! It traded the <em>values</em> but not locations of the two qubits!</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement><p>|11> or <datafile label="Balls11" filename="Balls11.png" include-source="yes">
          <image source="Balls11.png" width="66%"/>
        </datafile></p></statement>
        <feedback><p>Make sure you hooked up your circuit correctly!</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
    <hint><p>Make the circuit and look at the bar graph below the circuit. 
      The answer is the choice on the bar graph at 100%</p></hint>
  </exercise>

  <p>
    Now use the circuit builder to figure out the output when you give a SWAP gate 
